    "comment": "Rationale: The paper looks at muscarinic receptor modulation of the K+ evoked release of radiolabelled Acetylcholine (Figure 1B) , pre-incubated in brain slices, by generic muscarinic receptor agonist oxotremorine . The profound inhibition mediated by this agonist in hippocampal (Figure 2) and Cortical (Figure 3) brain slices slices from wild type mice is compared with those from mChR2 knockout mice.\n\n18/01/2018 Pim\n- The ACh-release experiments are on slices and do not provide a direct synaptic context. The synaptic context is provided by the localization studies in Fig.5+6 that show co-localization of CHRM2 and the vesicular ACh transporter (only striatum shown).. Experimental description: Materials and methods: The generation of homozygous M2 receptor KO (genetic background: 129J1 x CF1)........................................",
